HEADWORD: Grisaille
<hw>Gri"saille`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., from gris
gray.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>Decorative painting
in gray monochrome; -- used in English especially for painted
glass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of French fancy dress goods.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grisamber</ent>⟦br⟧
